title: In Ancient Forest, a Tiny Hummingbird Fights to Survive
description: Deep in the Ecuadorian Andes, an ancient forest stands as a final sanctuary against the encroachment of human activity. This is the Yanacocha Reserve, the last refuge for the Black-breasted puffleg (Eriocnemis nigrivestis), a tiny hummingbird teetering on the edge of extinction. Measuring just 3.5 inches, this emblematic bird...

title: Letter to the editor: 'Heritage emergency' declaration within the ancient parish West of Ifield
description: Declaration of a Heritage Emergency within the ancient Parish-West of Ifield has been announced, following the important precedent set this month by Stoke-on-Trent, which has become the first place in the UK to formally declare a Heritage Emergency ['Warning bells west of Ifield', Crawley Observer, Jan 26]
